	http://www.cnblogs.com/sea-wind/p/4176997.html<br /><br /><br /><blockquote style="margin: 20px 0px; padding: 20px 50px; border: 2px solid #efefef; color: #333333; border-radius: 10px; font-family: 微软雅黑; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20.8800010681152px; background: url('http://www.cnblogs.com/skins/iMetro/images/quote.png) -75px -20px no-repeat #f0f0f0"><p style="margin: 10px auto; padding: 0px">现在，我面对的书籍中，到处都充斥着矩阵或是向量，所以矩阵分析定是很重要的吧。抱着这个想法，我选修了&ldquo;矩阵分析&rdquo;这门课。然而我总是觉得老师、课本以一种怎么让我难受怎么讲的方式讲授矩阵。但待学完这门课程后，按自己的思路梳理一遍所学知识，又有了一种豁然开朗的感觉。<span style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #ff0000">本文将按照我个人的思路，阐明矩阵各个概念出现的联系或是因果关系。</span></p></blockquote><h2 style="margin: 15px auto 2px; padding: 0px; font-size: 21px; font-family: 微软雅黑">1. 为何要引入矩阵</h2><p style="margin: 10px auto; padding: 0px; font-family: 微软雅黑; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20.8800010681152px">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 这个问题很好解释，矩阵使得公式表达更加的方便。就这一便利性而言就值得引入矩阵这一概念，譬如：</p><p style="margin: 10px auto; padding: 0px; font-family: 微软雅黑; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20.8800010681152px" align="center"><img style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px" src="http://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?%5C%5C%20a_%7B11%7Dx_%7B11%7D&amp;plus;a_%7B12%7Dx_%7B12%7D&amp;plus;...&amp;plus;a_%7B1n%7Dx_%7B1n%7D%3Db_1%20%5C%5C%20a_%7B21%7Dx_%7B21%7D&amp;plus;a_%7B22%7Dx_%7B22%7D&amp;plus;...&amp;plus;a_%7B2n%7Dx_%7B2n%7D%3Db_2%20%5C%5C%20...%20%5C%5C%20a_%7Bm1%7Dx_%7Bm1%7D&amp;plus;a_%7Bm2%7Dx_%7Bm2%7D&amp;plus;...&amp;plus;a_%7Bmn%7Dx_%7Bmn%7D%3Db_m%20%5C%5C" border="0" title="This is the rendered form of the equation. You can not edit this directly. Right click will give you the option to save the image, and in most browsers you can drag the image onto your desktop or another program." /></p><p style="margin: 10px auto; padding: 0px; font-family: 微软雅黑; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20.8800010681152px" align="left">&nbsp;&nbsp; 在引入基本的矩阵乘法之后，就可以将上述的方程组表达成为<img style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px" src="http://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?AX%3D%5Cmathbf%7Bb%7D" border="0" title="This is the rendered form of the equation. You can not edit this directly. Right click will give you the option to save the image, and in most browsers you can drag the image onto your desktop or another program." />，其中&nbsp;<span style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; display: inline; line-height: normal; word-spacing: normal; word-wrap: normal; white-space: nowrap; float: none; direction: ltr; max-width: none; max-height: none; min-width: 0px; min-height: 0px; border: 0px" class="MathJax"><span style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-transition: none; transition: none; display: inline-block; position: static; border: 0px; vertical-align: 0px; width: 5.579em" class="math"><span style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-transition: none; transition: none; display: inline-block; position: relative; border: 0px; vertical-align: 0px; width: 4.429em; height: 0px; font-size: 17px"><span style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-transition: none; transition: none; position: absolute; border: 0px; vertical-align: 0px; clip: rect(1.785em 1000.012em 2.992em -0.457em); top: -2.756em; left: 0.003em"><span style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-transition: none; transition: none; display: inline; position: static; border: 0px; vertical-align: 0px" class="mrow"><span style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; transition: none; -webkit-transition: none; display: inline; position: static; border: 0px; vertical-align: 0px; font-family: MathJax_Math-italic" class="mi">A</span><span style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0.29em; transition: none; -webkit-transition: none; display: inline; position: static; border: 0px; vertical-align: 0px; font-family: MathJax_Main" class="mo">&isin;</span><span style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0.29em; -webkit-transition: none; transition: none; display: inline; position: static; border: 0px; vertical-align: 0px" class="msubsup"><span style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-transition: none; transition